COMPONENT NAME: IKM SQL to JMS Append
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module - Inserts data in a JMS Message from any ISO-92 compliant staging area.
Restrictions: - Options : CLIENTID, DURABLE, MESSAGEMAXNUMBER, MESSAGETIMEOUT, NEXTMESSAGETIMEOUT, MESSAGESELECTOR are not used. They should be set to a null value. - When using this module with a journalized source table, data are automatically filtered to not include source deletions
Check this option if you want to publish new messages in the destination
Uncheck this option to not commit your publication on your routeur. This option is set to true by default.
Set the JMS Delivery Mode value
Set the JMS Delivery Mode value. 1 = Not Persistent. 2 = Persistent
Expiration delay in milliseconds for the message. 0 = Infinite. 4,000,000 = maximum value
Priority for the message. Any value between 0 (highest priority) and 9 (Lowest priority).
Type of message to send. 1 = BytesMessage. 2 = Text Message
Optional name of the message (data structure)

<%for (int i=0; i < odiRef.getDataSetCount(); i++){%> <%=odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator")%> select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[EXPRESSION]\t[ALIAS_SEP] [CX_COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom(i)%> where <% if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { %> JRN_FLAG <> 'D' <%} else {%> (1=1) <% } %> <%=odiRef.getJoin(i)%> <%=odiRef.getFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy(i)%> <%=odiRef.getHaving(i)%> <%}%>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
